Maintainer: Giuseppe Arena <g.arena@uva.nl>
Description: Tools for fitting, diagnozing, and analyzing relational event models. There is support for tie-oriented modeling (Butts, C., 2008, <doi:10.1111/j.1467-9531.2008.00203.x>) and an actor-oriented modeling framework (Stadtfeld, C., & Block, P., 2017, <doi:10.15195/v4.a14>). The package accommodates both frequentist and Bayesian approaches. There is support for modeling of events with a duration, for random effects models (e.g., frailty relational event models), discrete mixture models (e.g., dyadic latent class modeling), and penalized approaches (e.g., using the lasso). 
